This topic falls under several sub-categories of computer science, including discrete mathematics (cs.DM), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), stochastic processes (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT). Given the focus on graph theory and stochastic processes, cs.GT and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of asymptotic analysis and bounds suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and data structures and algorithms, hence cs.DM and cs.DS are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper does not explicitly deal with information theory, but the use of random walks and probability suggests a possible connection, hence cs.IT is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
